.TH "drm_mode_obj_get_properties_ioctl" 9 "drm_mode_obj_get_properties_ioctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_obj_get_properties_ioctl \- get the current value of a object's property
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_mode_obj_get_properties_ioctl
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "struct drm_file *file_priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "data" 12
ioctl data
.IP "file_priv" 12
DRM file info
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function retrieves the current value for an object's property. Compared
to the connector specific ioctl this one is extended to also work on crtc and
plane objects.

Called by the user via ioctl.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative errno on failure.
